# Broadwater, Western Australia

**Broadwater** is a suburb of the Western Australian city of [Busselton](/Busselton). At the [2021 census](/2021_Australian_census), it had a population of 4,269. Broadwater is known for its scenic beauty, proximity to the foreshore at [Geographe Bay](/Geographe_Bay), and a mix of residential areas and tourist accommodations.

## History

Broadwater was gazetted in 1897. Initially, it encompassed the area that is now the Busselton suburb of [Abbey](/Abbey,_Western_Australia). The suburb has evolved significantly over the years, transitioning from a small settlement to a vibrant community with a blend of residential and tourist facilities.

## Geography

Broadwater is located approximately 6 kilometers (3.7 miles) from the city center of [Busselton](/Busselton). It is situated within the [City of Busselton](/City_of_Busselton) local government area. The suburb is characterized by its proximity to the beautiful [Geographe Bay](/Geographe_Bay), which offers stunning coastal views and recreational opportunities.

## Demographics

According to the [2021 Australian census](/2021_Australian_census), Broadwater had a population of 4,269. The suburb is a mix of permanent residents and seasonal visitors, attracted by the scenic beauty and tourist amenities.

## Economy and Tourism

Broadwater's economy is significantly influenced by tourism. The suburb contains a variety of tourist accommodation providers, including hotels, motels, and holiday rentals. These establishments take advantage of the suburb's proximity to the foreshore at [Geographe Bay](/Geographe_Bay), making it a popular destination for both domestic and international tourists.

One notable landmark in Broadwater was the [drive-in cinema](/Drive-in_cinema), which was built in 1960. By the time of its closure in 2015, it was one of the last such structures in Western Australia, serving as a nostalgic reminder of the mid-20th century entertainment culture.

## Governance

Broadwater is governed by the [City of Busselton](/City_of_Busselton). The suburb falls within the [Vasse](/Electoral_district_of_Vasse) state electorate and the [Forrest](/Division_of_Forrest) federal division.

## Education and Infrastructure

Broadwater is well-served by educational institutions and infrastructure. The suburb has access to various schools and community facilities, ensuring a high quality of life for its residents. The proximity to [Busselton](/Busselton) provides additional amenities and services.